-- South African Wine-Grape Crop Expected to Rise 7.3% to 1.35 Million Tons
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-12-08T13:52:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-08/south-african-wine-grape-crop-expected-to-rise-7-3-to-1-35-million-tons.html
 South Africa’s 2011 wine-grape crop
should amount to 1.35 million metric tons, a 7.3 percent
increase on this year’s harvest, South African Wine Industry
Information & Systems said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  